SIMPLE: supraoccipital
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supraoccipital
<hw>Su`pra*oc*cip"i*tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Situated over, or in the upper part of, the
occiput; of or pertaining to the supraoccipital bone.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The supraoccipital bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Supraoccipital bone</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>a
bone on the dorsal side of the great foramen of the skull, usually
forming a part of the occipital in the adult, but distinct in the
young.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supraocular</ent>⟦br⟧
